issue.body:
The `get_compiled_select('', FALSE)` does indeed not reset the select, but it generates errors on the next `get()` or `count_all_results()` if a where() clause is included.

I've been trying to modify the `count_all_results()` method to also include a reset_select override. The problem is the `_compile_select()` method, because it escapes identifiers and compiles various parts of the query (<i><b>edit</b>: it collapses the qb_where, qb_group_by and other arrays</i>). Any next call to QB, including a where clause, to get or count rows will generate an error on compile methods, because the parts are already compiled.
### Reproduce error

There are several issues:

``` php
        // issue 1: multiple table names are being added
        $foo = $this->db
          ->select('id, title');
        echo '<br>' . $foo->get_compiled_select('agenda', FALSE);
        echo '<br>' . $foo->get_compiled_select('agenda', FALSE);
        echo '<br>' . $foo->get_compiled_select('agenda', FALSE);

        // result:
        // SELECT `id`, `title` FROM `agenda`
        // SELECT `id`, `title` FROM `agenda`, `agenda`
        // SELECT `id`, `title` FROM `agenda`, `agenda`, `agenda`
```

.

``` php
        // issue 2: adding where clause causes errors
        // (include a from('agenda') to work-around issue 1)
        $foo = $this->db
          ->select('id, title')
          ->from('agenda')
          ->where('id', 938);
        echo '<br>' . $foo->get_compiled_select('', FALSE);
        echo '<br>' . $foo->get_compiled_select('', FALSE); // or $foo->get();

        // result:
        // SELECT `id`, `title` FROM `agenda`
        //  | PHP Error was encountered
        //  | Message: Illegal string offset 'escape'
        //  | Filename: database/DB_query_builder.php
```
### Workaround

The count_all_results doesn't have a reset_select override<sup>(1)</sup>. When i tried to implement a simple reset=false, like in compile_select, was when i stumbled on the above issues. A work-around is to first store all the query parts, and restore them after the count query has run.

``` php
    public function count_all_results($table = '', $reset_select = TRUE)
    {
        if ($reset_select == FALSE)
        {
            // NEW: store the values before running the query
            $temp = array(
                'qb_select'         => $this->qb_select,
                'qb_from'           => $this->qb_from,
                'qb_join'           => $this->qb_join,
                'qb_where'          => $this->qb_where,
                'qb_groupby'        => $this->qb_groupby,
                'qb_having'         => $this->qb_having,
                'qb_orderby'        => $this->qb_orderby,
                'qb_aliased_tables' => $this->qb_aliased_tables,
                'qb_no_escape'      => $this->qb_no_escape,
                'qb_distinct'       => $this->qb_distinct,
                'qb_limit'          => $this->qb_limit,
                'qb_offset'         => $this->qb_offset,
            );
        }

        if ($table !== '')
        {
            $this->_track_aliases($table);
            $this->from($table);
        }

        $result = ($this->qb_distinct === TRUE)
            ? $this->query($this->_count_string.$this->protect_identifiers('numrows')."\nFROM (\n".$this->_compile_select()."\n) CI_count_all_results")
            : $this->query($this->_compile_select($this->_count_string.$this->protect_identifiers('numrows')));

        if ($reset_select)
        {
            $this->_reset_select();
        }
        else
        {
            // NEW: restore the values
            $this->_reset_run($temp);
        }

        if ($result->num_rows() === 0)
        {
            return 0;
        }

        $row = $result->row();
        return (int) $row->numrows;
    }
```

_<sup>(1)</sup>Note: the override for reset_select in  `count_all_results()` from #1982 seems never to have been implemented / merged._

